ics as a context for interpreting US history. Gamwell then defends his metaphysics against both modern refusals of metaphysics and accounts of ultimate reality offered by Niebuhr and Murdoch.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aDemocracyxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aReligion and politicszUnited States. 4aPhilosophy : Ethics. 4aPhilosophy : Metaphysics. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Theology. 7aRELIGION / Theism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2015z978311149061840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143845809040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438458090423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438458090/original  a978-3-11-149061-8  SUNY Press eBook Package 2015b2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles